## Complete API Reference for .NET 10 AI Tool Calling

Based on the NuGet package XML documentation, here's the exact API patterns you should use:

---

### **1. Microsoft.Extensions.AI (v9.10.2)**

#### **ChatClientBuilder** - Extension method from abstractions
```csharp
// Create a builder from an existing IChatClient
var builder = chatClient.AsBuilder();  // Extension method in abstractions

// Or direct constructor
var builder = new ChatClientBuilder(innerClient);
```

#### **UseFunctionInvocation Extension Method**
```csharp
// Method signature:
ChatClientBuilder.UseFunctionInvocation(
    ILoggerFactory loggerFactory, 
    Action<FunctionInvokingChatClient>? configure = null)
    : ChatClientBuilder
```
**Note:** This is in `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.FunctionInvokingChatClientBuilderExtensions`

#### **AIFunctionFactory.Create Overloads**
```csharp
// Create from delegate
AIFunction AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    Delegate method,
    AIFunctionFactoryOptions? options = null)

// Create from delegate with custom metadata
AIFunction AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    Delegate method,
    string? name = null,
    string? description = null,
    JsonSerializerOptions? jsonSerializerOptions = null)

// Create from MethodInfo with instance
AIFunction AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    MethodInfo method,
    object? target,  // null for static methods
    AIFunctionFactoryOptions? options = null)

// Create from MethodInfo with custom metadata
AIFunction AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    MethodInfo method,
    object? target,
    string? name = null,
    string? description = null,
    JsonSerializerOptions? jsonSerializerOptions = null)

// Create from MethodInfo with factory delegate (for factory pattern)
AIFunction AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    MethodInfo method,
    Func<AIFunctionArguments, object> instanceFactory,
    AIFunctionFactoryOptions? options = null)

// Create a declaration only (non-invocable)
AIFunctionDeclaration AIFunctionFactory.CreateDeclaration(
    string name,
    string description,
    JsonElement jsonSchema,
    JsonElement? returnJsonSchema = null)
```

#### **AIFunction Class**
```csharp
public class AIFunction : AIFunctionDeclaration
{
    // Invoke the function with arguments
    public async Task<object?> InvokeAsync(
        AIFunctionArguments arguments,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    // Get the underlying MethodInfo if wrapped
    public MethodInfo? UnderlyingMethod { get; }

    // Convert to declaration-only version
    public AIFunctionDeclaration AsDeclarationOnly()
}
```

#### **ChatOptions Class**
```csharp
public class ChatOptions
{
    public ChatOptions() { }
    public ChatOptions(ChatOptions other) { }  // Copy constructor

    // Collection of tools (AIFunction or other AITool implementations)
    public IList<AITool>? Tools { get; set; }

    // Other notable properties:
    public string? ConversationId { get; set; }
    public int? MaxTokens { get; set; }
    public float? Temperature { get; set; }
    public IList<string>? StopSequences { get; set; }
    public ChatToolMode? ToolMode { get; set; }
    public IDictionary<string, object?>? AdditionalProperties { get; set; }

    // Clone method (shallow copy of collections)
    public virtual ChatOptions Clone()
}
```

---

### **2. Microsoft.Extensions.AI.Abstractions (v9.10.2)**

#### **IChatClient Interface**
```csharp
public interface IChatClient
{
    // Primary methods for getting responses
    Task<ChatResponse> GetResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> chatMessages,
        ChatOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    // Streaming variant
    IAsyncEnumerable<ChatResponseUpdate> GetStreamingResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> chatMessages,
        ChatOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    // Service resolution
    TService? GetService<TService>(object? serviceKey = null)
}

// Extension methods on IChatClient
public static class ChatClientExtensions
{
    // Convenience method for string input
    public static Task<ChatResponse> GetResponseAsync(
        this IChatClient client,
        string userMessage,
        ChatOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    // Many other convenience overloads...
}
```

#### **ChatMessage Constructors**
```csharp
public class ChatMessage
{
    // Default constructor (creates User role message)
    public ChatMessage()

    // String content constructor
    public ChatMessage(ChatRole role, string text)

    // Complex content constructor
    public ChatMessage(ChatRole role, IList<AIContent> content)

    public ChatRole Role { get; set; }
    public IList<AIContent> Content { get; set; }

    public ChatMessage Clone()
}
```

#### **ChatRole Constants**
```csharp
public class ChatRole : IEquatable<ChatRole>
{
    // Role constants (static properties)
    public static ChatRole System { get; }      // System instructions
    public static ChatRole Assistant { get; }   // AI response
    public static ChatRole User { get; }        // User input
    public static ChatRole Tool { get; }        // Tool results

    public string Value { get; }  // String representation
}
```

#### **ChatResponse Class**
```csharp
public class ChatResponse
{
    public ChatResponse() { }
    public ChatResponse(ChatMessage message) { }
    public ChatResponse(IList<ChatMessage> messages) { }

    public IList<ChatMessage> Messages { get; }  // Response messages
    public ChatFinishReason? FinishReason { get; }
    public int? CompletionTokenCount { get; }
    public int? PromptTokenCount { get; }
    public IDictionary<string, object?>? AdditionalProperties { get; }
}
```

#### **ChatResponseUpdate (for streaming)**
```csharp
public class ChatResponseUpdate
{
    public ChatRole? Role { get; }
    public AIContent? Content { get; }  // Incremental content
    public ChatFinishReason? FinishReason { get; }
    // ... other properties
}
```

#### **AITool Base Class**
```csharp
public class AITool
{
    public string? Name { get; }
    public string? Description { get; }
    public IDictionary<string, object?>? AdditionalProperties { get; }

    // Service resolution
    public TService? GetService<TService>(object? serviceKey = null)
}
```

#### **AIFunction Extends AIFunctionDeclaration**
```csharp
public class AIFunctionDeclaration : AITool
{
    // JSON schema describing the function
    public JsonElement? JsonSchema { get; }

    // Return type schema (optional)
    public JsonElement? ReturnJsonSchema { get; }
}

public class AIFunction : AIFunctionDeclaration
{
    // Invocable - see above
}
```

#### **AIFunctionArguments**
```csharp
public class AIFunctionArguments : Dictionary<string, object?>
{
    public IServiceProvider? ServiceProvider { get; set; }
}
```

---

### **3. Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI (v10.3.0)**

#### **OpenAI Client Extension Method**
```csharp
// Namespace: Microsoft.Extensions.AI
// Extension class: OpenAIClientExtensions

public static IChatClient AsIChatClient(this OpenAI.Chat.ChatClient chatClient)

public static IChatClient AsIChatClient(
    this OpenAI.Assistants.AssistantClient assistantClient,
    string assistantId,
    string? threadId = null)

public static IChatClient AsIChatClient(
    this OpenAI.Responses.ResponsesClient responseClient)

// Returns: IChatClient wrapper around OpenAI client
```

**Note:** The method is `AsIChatClient()` (not `AsChatClient()`)

---

### **4. Microsoft.Agents.AI (v1.3.0)**

#### **AIAgent Abstract Base Class**
```csharp
public abstract class AIAgent
{
    // Properties
    public string Id { get; }
    public string? Name { get; }
    public string? Description { get; }
    public AgentRunContext? CurrentRunContext { get; }

    // Session management
    public Task<AgentSession> CreateSessionAsync(
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    // Core run methods (multiple overloads for different inputs)
    public Task<AgentResponse> RunAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> chatMessages,
        AgentSession session,
        AgentRunOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    public Task<AgentResponse> RunAsync(
        string userMessage,
        AgentSession session,
        AgentRunOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    public Task<AgentResponse> RunAsync(
        ChatMessage chatMessage,
        AgentSession session,
        AgentRunOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    public Task<AgentResponse> RunAsync(
        AgentSession session,
        AgentRunOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    // Streaming variants
    public IAsyncEnumerable<AgentResponseUpdate> RunStreamingAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> chatMessages,
        AgentSession session,
        AgentRunOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)

    // Typed response (deserialized to T)
    public Task<T> RunAsync<T>(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> chatMessages,
        AgentSession session,
        JsonSerializerOptions? jsonOptions = null,
        AgentRunOptions? options = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)
}
```

#### **AIAgentBuilder**
```csharp
public class AIAgentBuilder
{
    // Constructors
    public AIAgentBuilder(AIAgent innerAgent)
    public AIAgentBuilder(Func<IServiceProvider, AIAgent> innerAgentFactory)

    // Build the pipeline
    public AIAgent Build(IServiceProvider? serviceProvider = null)

    // Add middleware/decorators
    public AIAgentBuilder Use(
        Func<AIAgent, AIAgent> middleware)

    public AIAgentBuilder Use(
        Func<AIAgent, IServiceProvider, AIAgent> middleware)
}

// Extension method to create builder from existing agent
public static class AIAgentExtensions
{
    public static AIAgentBuilder AsBuilder(this AIAgent innerAgent)
}
```

#### **AgentSession**
```csharp
public abstract class AgentSession
{
    public AgentSessionStateBag StateBag { get; }

    // Service resolution
    public TService? GetService<TService>(object? serviceKey = null)
}

public class AgentSessionStateBag
{
    public int Count { get; }

    // Type-safe state management
    public bool TryGetValue<T>(
        string key,
        out T? value,
        JsonSerializerOptions? jsonOptions = null)

    public T? GetValue<T>(
        string key,
        JsonSerializerOptions? jsonOptions = null)

    public void SetValue<T>(
        string key,
        T? value,
        JsonSerializerOptions? jsonOptions = null)

    public bool TryRemoveValue(string key)

    public JsonElement Serialize()
    public static AgentSessionStateBag Deserialize(JsonElement json)
}
```

#### **Agent as a Function**
```csharp
public static class AIAgentExtensions
{
    // Convert agent to invocable function
    public static AIFunction AsAIFunction(
        this AIAgent agent,
        AIFunctionFactoryOptions? options = null,
        AgentSession? session = null)

    // Returns: AIFunction that can be used as a tool by other agents
}
```

#### **AgentRunContext & AgentResponse**
```csharp
public class AgentRunContext
{
    public AIAgent Agent { get; }
    public AgentSession Session { get; }
    public IReadOnlyCollection<ChatMessage> Messages { get; }
    public AgentRunOptions? Options { get; }
}

public class AgentResponse
{
    public IEnumerable<ChatMessage> Messages { get; }
    public string? SessionState { get; }
}

public class AgentResponseUpdate
{
    public string? Content { get; }
    // Incremental streaming data
}

public class AgentRunOptions
{
    // Configuration for agent run
    public int? MaxIterations { get; set; }
}
```

---

## **Key Patterns for Tool Calling**

### **Pattern 1: Create and invoke a tool directly**
```csharp
// Create function from delegate
var addFunc = AIFunctionFactory.Create(
    (int a, int b) => a + b,
    name: "add",
    description: "Adds two numbers"
);

// Or from method info
var method = typeof(MyClass).GetMethod("Add");
var func = AIFunctionFactory.Create(method, null);
```

### **Pattern 2: Set up chat with tools**
```csharp
var options = new ChatOptions
{
    Tools = new List<AITool> { addFunc, subtractFunc },
    ToolMode = ChatToolMode.RequireAny  // Force tool use
};

var response = await chatClient.GetResponseAsync(
    new[] { new ChatMessage(ChatRole.User, "What is 5 + 3?") },
    options
);
```

### **Pattern 3: Full pipeline with function invocation**
```csharp
var chatClient = openAIClient.AsIChatClient();  // Convert OpenAI client

var builder = chatClient.AsBuilder()
    .UseFunctionInvocation(loggerFactory)  // Auto-invoke functions
    .Build();

// Now chatClient automatically invokes functions
```

### **Pattern 4: Agent loop with tools**
```csharp
var agent = new ChatClientAgent(chatClient, options)
{
    Name = "MyAgent",
    Description = "An agent with tools"
};

var session = await agent.CreateSessionAsync();

var response = await agent.RunAsync(
    "Solve this problem using the available tools",
    session
);
```

---

## **Key Differences from Other APIs:**

- **Method name:** `GetResponseAsync()` (NOT `CompleteAsync()`)
- **OpenAI extension:** `AsIChatClient()` (NOT `AsChatClient()`)
- **Tools property:** `ChatOptions.Tools` is `IList<AITool>?`
- **Response type:** `ChatResponse` (NOT `ChatCompletion`)
- **Chat roles:** Static properties on `ChatRole` class (e.g., `ChatRole.User`, `ChatRole.Assistant`)

